net.hudup.core.data

Class NominalList

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.NominalList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, TextParsable

    public class NominalList
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, Cloneable, TextParsable
    This class represent a list of nominal (s), called nominal list, in brief. Recall that nominal data indicates discrete and non-number data such as weekdays {Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday}. Nominal data is called nominal, in brief, represented by Nominal class. A nominal is always in this nominal list and so it has an index in this nominal list. Nominal list can have hierarchical structure, for example, in the nominal list {fruit, table, apple, orange}, nominal (s) "apple" and "orange" are children of parent nominal "fruit". Nominal list uses a Map to store nominal (s) instead of using List. Such map is referred by the variable map. Each entry in this map is a key-value pair in which the value is a nominal and the key indicates the index of such nominal.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
